# $project_name

Built with [LangGraph.js](https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraphjs) and [Aegra](https://github.com/ibbybuilds/aegra) — a self-hosted LangSmith Deployments alternative.

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env       # Configure your environment
npm install                # Install Node.js dependencies
pip install aegra-cli      # Install Aegra CLI (if not already)
aegra dev                  # Start developing!
```

## Project Structure

```
$slug/
|-- aegra.json            # Graph configuration
|-- package.json          # Node.js dependencies
|-- tsconfig.json         # TypeScript configuration
|-- .env.example          # Environment variable template
|-- src/$slug/
|   |-- graph.ts          # Your agent graph
|   +-- state.ts          # State annotations
|-- docker-compose.yml    # Docker Compose (PostgreSQL + API)
+-- Dockerfile
```

## Development

Start the development server:

```bash
aegra dev
```

This will:
1. Start PostgreSQL via Docker Compose
2. Auto-install Node.js dependencies
3. Launch the Aegra API server on port 2026

## Usage

Use the LangGraph SDK to interact with your agent:

```python
from langgraph_sdk import get_client

client = get_client(url="http://localhost:2026")
thread = await client.threads.create()

async for chunk in client.runs.stream(
    thread_id=thread["thread_id"],
    assistant_id="$slug",
    input={"messages": [{"type": "human", "content": "Hello!"}]},
):
    print(chunk)
```
